# MedPulse AI — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
- Educational medical platform for Arab medical students
- Next.js 15 App Router + TypeScript strict + Supabase + Grok API
- Multi-source medical evidence aggregation system
- NOT for clinical diagnosis — educational only

## Before Writing Any Code
1. Read `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
2. Read `docs/PATTERNS.md`
3. Search the codebase for similar functionality
4. If similar pattern exists, EXTEND it — don't create new

## Architecture Rules (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
- Single Grok client: `lib/services/ai/grok-client.ts`
- Single Supabase access: `lib/repositories/`
- Business logic: `lib/services/` only
- API routes: thin (validate, call service, return)

## Code Style
- Functions < 50 lines
- Files < 300 lines
- No `any` without `// @ts-expect-error: <reason>`
- All async ops: try/catch with typed errors
- All fetches: `AbortSignal.timeout(10000)`
- All inputs: validate with Zod

## Forbidden
- ❌ Duplicating logic across files
- ❌ Bypassing repositories for DB access
- ❌ Inline business logic in routes/components
- ❌ Hardcoded API URLs
- ❌ `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`
- ❌ Exposing internal errors in production
- ❌ Adding features without updating docs

## When Adding Features
1. Update `docs/PATTERNS.md` if new pattern
2. Update `docs/DECISIONS.md` if architectural choice
3. Add at least 1 test for critical path
4. JSDoc for public APIs

## When in Doubt
- Composition over inheritance
- Pure functions over classes
- Explicit over clever
- ASK before assuming